  <rte>
    <name>Bowfell and Esk Pike from Old Dungeon Ghyll</name>
    <desc>The high fells surrounding Scafell Pike all have their own character. This Lake District circular walk embraces two old favourites, Bowfell and Esk Pike, each having something different to offer the walker.</desc>
    <author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1157-description</url>
